      "title": "Homogenization of Reticulated Structures",
      "abstract": "Materials science is an area of growing research as composite materials become widely used in such areas as civil engineering, electrotechnics, and the aerospace industry. This mathematically rigorous treatment of lattice-type structures will appeal to both applied mathematicians, as well as engineers looking for a solid mathematical foundation of the methodology."
